Context

Purpose:
- Compact current context for MemoryEndpoints.com work without becoming a changelog or durable memory body.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with source, reports, and the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: compact project context, current objective shape, and active constraints.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this file when the compact current context changes; preserve implementation detail in current engineering docs, durable reviewed knowledge in MATM, and point-in-time evidence under ignored `var/reports/`.
Source of truth: `.uai/identity.uai`, `.uai/overview.uai`, `.uai/progress.uai`, and current repository state.
Next action for agents: use this as a compact orientation, then load the specialized typed file before acting on a topic.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private customer data, or private deployment values.

Current context:
- The active goal is to move the reports in `D:\DownloadArchive` into the database-backed MemoryEndpoints.com knowledge system one source at a time, creating context-rich company, workspace, and project wiki trees while improving the system through dogfooding.
- The repository has working local route, storage, package, secret-scan, `.uai`, static-site, and dogfood evidence.
- Latest-code MemoryEndpoints.com public deployment is verified through the FileZilla-backed explicit FTPS profile; MultiAgentMemory.com companion publishing is also live-verified through its FileZilla-backed FTPS profile.
- The database wiki has lifecycle-aware pages and first-class external-link search for `AI Agent Memory Architecture Research.md`, `AI Agent Memory Best Practices Research.md`, `MATM Architecture Design Research.md`, `AI Memory Governance Feedback Loop.md`, `AI Dreaming Memory Management for LLMWikis.org.md`, and `AI Agent Network Development Plan.md`.
- `AI Agent Memory Best Practices Research.md` is represented by one canonical current contract, one complete historical source, and nine focused pages. Its 46 numbered bibliography records were ingested one at a time, four independent authority records supplement review, and lifecycle labels distinguish current contracts, historical surveys, and unverified proposals.
- Source preflight is mandatory before every report or external-link write. Request fingerprints include the indexed body so exact replays remain idempotent while changed content creates a revision; report text omits embedded data images while retaining exact source, selection, and indexed-content hashes.
- Independent review corrected the source's model attribution and unsupported decay implications before promotion. Vendor evidence remains labeled as first-party evidence, weak/community evidence remains unreviewed, and repeated representations of one study are not counted as independent sources.
- `AI Agent Network Development Plan.md` is represented by one complete historical source, eight focused historical or proposed pages, and one current reviewed decision-boundary page. Its 26 URL-bearing numbered references were ingested one at a time and five independent primary sources supplement review; blanket API-elimination, protocol-mandate, cryptography-replaces-governance, automatic-decay, and universal confidential-computing claims were not promoted as current guidance.
- `AI Agent Ecosystem Participation Guide.md` is represented by one complete historical source, eight focused historical or proposed pages, and one current reviewed participation, risk, and human-governance page. Its 34 URL-bearing works-cited sources produced 35 contextual citations, while independent review brings the combined graph to 43 canonical links and 59 mentions; ten lifecycle-labeled memories are promoted.
- Current ecosystem guidance treats multi-agent gains as conditional, keeps human accountability and deterministic control gates, requires ownership and version-aware conflict handling for shared memory, limits MCP to context and tool integration, and rejects model-only moderation, cryptoeconomic authority, TEE untamperability, untested recovery promises, and unattended production updates.
- `AI Agent Integration with UAIX Standards.md` is represented by one complete historical source, five focused historical pages, two proposed pages, and one current reviewed company-level integration and trust-boundary page. Its 20 source-link records and 29 independent-review mentions form 33 reviewed canonical links and 49 contextual mentions; all nine lifecycle-labeled memories are promoted.
- Current UAIX integration guidance treats UAI-1 as portable exchange and evidence, Project Handoff and local `.uai` as repository context, MCP as host/tool/resource context, and implemented peer protocols as coordination. Capability, schema validity, declarations, and signatures never grant authorization; LocalEndpoint, Carcinus, NeuralWikis, and MemoryEndpoints retain separate product and trust boundaries.
- `AI Agent Sandbox Security Specification.md` is represented by one reviewer-authored current project decision, one complete historical source, five focused historical pages, and four proposed pages. Its 41 works-cited mentions and 34 independent-evidence mentions form 56 canonical links and 75 contextual mentions; all eleven lifecycle-labeled memories are promoted.
- Current execution-security guidance keeps MemoryEndpoints as a protected memory and coordination service rather than an arbitrary-code host, treats current Carcinus as a public profile and coordination product rather than an implemented sandbox, selects isolation from a concrete threat model, and rejects absolute guarantees, schema-only authority, MCP-manifest authority, silent no-op, fixed loop heuristics as proof, and unreviewed snapshot reuse.
- The sandbox decision page has five current internal-contract links and sixteen described primary references. Anonymous document and link APIs deny access without title or source leakage; authenticated internal navigation retains access, desktop and true narrow-mobile geometry show no page overflow, the wide comparison table stays contained in its scroll wrapper, and browser diagnostics are clean.
- `AI Agent Sprint Plan for NeuralWikis.md` is represented by one reviewer-authored current project decision, one complete historical source, five focused historical pages, and three proposed pages. Six pages are project-owned, three are workspace-owned, and one company page captures cross-product delivery governance. Forty source citations plus nineteen current-evidence mentions form 48 canonical links and 59 contextual mentions; all ten lifecycle-labeled memories are promoted.
- Current agent-callable integration guidance preserves private tenant knowledge and human accessibility, uses current HTTP and MCP contracts under service authorization, treats crawler and manifest files as hints rather than authority, bounds idempotency and rollback to implemented semantics, and adds machine-readable evidence and compute/reviewer budgets without transferring accountable product or release authority to agents.
- Dogfooding the source exposed that an unreviewed citation could downgrade an already reviewed canonical link and that raw crawl-policy text could fail normalized readback. Storage now preserves explicit review dispositions for incidental unreviewed mentions, the client canonicalizes crawl policy, and focused plus full integration coverage proves the behavior.
- The current documentation cycle replaces stale route counts, upload counts, backend state, and incomplete route narratives with a source-tested GitHub route inventory, deep system architecture, and a complete MultiAgentMemory.com API/data reference. Generated evidence belongs under ignored `var/reports/`; checked-in report snapshots are historical only.
- The current implementation adds a protected virtual UAIX package for TinyRustLM-class accountless browser agents with no durable local filesystem. It binds package identity to workspace plus registered agent, validates date-free typed public-safe records, retains immutable revisions, and returns deterministic startup readiness.
- The same implementation adds a separate hash-only local `.uai` collaboration overlay for simultaneous filesystem agents. It stores no local file body; overlapping claims and stale base hashes stop safely and point agents toward project-room coordination and normal source-control reconciliation.
- Local integration, documentation freshness, static companion, and `.uai` audit checks pass for the virtual-package and collaboration routes. Their exact-revision deployment, production MySQL contract/package/claim verification, MemoryEndpoints publication, and MultiAgentMemory publication are live-verified; every later commit must repeat those release gates before the claim remains current.
- The knowledge surface is private by invariant: `/knowledge` is only an empty authentication shell, all wiki/search/external-link data requires a workspace-bound key, and durable knowledge belongs only to company, workspace, or project. Accounts/users are many-to-many company members and do not own knowledge trees.
- Authenticated wiki pages use clean internal `/knowledge/company|workspace|project/...` routes. A deep route returns only the empty private shell before authentication, resolves through an exact workspace-bound database query after authentication, and keeps browser history inside the authenticated wiki surface.
- The ingestion tool accepts rendered Markdown headings whose source punctuation is backslash-escaped; regression tests cover the behavior.
- The ingestion tool ignores ATX-looking headings inside fenced and indented code so embedded schema examples remain within their real report section; full local, aggregate, exact-SHA deployment, production MySQL, combined dogfood, and human-wiki verification pass.
- `Small-Model Architecture Research.md` is represented by thirteen reviewed proposed TinyRustLM.com project pages and thirteen individually promoted memories under `/knowledge/project/tinyrustlm-model-architecture/`. The cycle retains one exact source hash, three taxonomy paths per page, thirty-seven canonical links, fifty-five contextual mentions, and explicit evidence gates rather than declaring a model compatible, approved, or legally cleared.
- Citation dogfooding moved source-report provenance from canonical-link metadata to each mention. Memory dogfooding added stem-aware contextual ranking, normalized storage-size units, and source-linked protected-wiki evidence while retaining exact identifier, scope, lifecycle, review, and promotion behavior.
- The authenticated narrow-screen wiki now reveals a requested protected article before the bounded taxonomy tree and puts active search results ahead of navigation. Production mobile and desktop browser checks, the complete test suite, exact source SHA, MySQL, route, UAIX-package, and connector-contract checks pass for the current release.
- TinyRustLM implementation coordination is split deliberately: the virtual UAI browser-connector contract is the current task lane, while the bounded OPFS worker-loader task remains queued. MemoryEndpoints owns canonical one-source-at-a-time enterprise ingestion; TinyRustLM owns only project implementation artifacts and evidence.
- Twelve independent reports remain queued in `D:\DownloadArchive` as six paired research perspectives. Each source requires its own preflight, review, scoped pages, citations, memories, readback, and learned-system update; paired reports must not be collapsed or processed concurrently.
- Local dogfood selects an isolated SQLite database explicitly instead of inheriting the production MySQL profile through the obsolete JSON-store environment path. Fresh command evidence satisfies readiness only after a successful check, while tracked evidence remains the fallback.
- The `.uai` suite remains active memory and forbidden duration/state filenames are not allowed as actual local files. The accountless-browser database profile can represent its configuration-specific short-term logical role without creating a file.
- Active handoff buckets must be empty or placeholder-only after processed intake is archived or otherwise dispositioned.
